He  said, “They came to my house at about 1:30 a.m. I was not at home then,  but they forced themselves into my house and asked my wife where I was  and she told them I was not at home.

“They destroyed my  television set and refrigerator before taking my wife and son insisting  that my wife must take them to where I was.One of my neighbour’s, who  works with the FRSC, Sabitu Abdulhamid, was shot dead by the kidnappers  when he rushed out in an attempt to save my family.

“The kidnappers have not made any contact yet,” Mr. Birnin-Yero said

The  FRSC Sector Commander in the state, Umar Ibrahim, confirmed the death  of the corps personnel and described the incident as very unfortunate.

Mr. Ibrahim described the deceased as a very hard working person, who was also a member of the community’s vigilante.

“I  am just coming back from the burial. It is a sad day for members of his  family and the entire FRSC family, “the sector commander said.